sphere  of 1 foot in radius for every level of the caster. The initial damage
caused  by  the spell is 1d4+2 points of fire damage for every level  of  the
caster, save versus spell for half damage.
           The gift that keeps on giving. Everyone within the initial area of
effect  who  missed  their saving throw versus spell will take  1d4+(caster's
level)  points  of fire damage from the superheated paste adhering  to  their
person.  This  damage  continues  for the caster's  level  in  combat  rounds
irrespective  of  where the individual moves. A saving  throw  versus  dragon
breath  will  result in half damage. Two consecutive saving  throws  indicate
that  the  paste has burned out (the saving throw versus the initial fireball
counts  towards these two consecutive saving throws) and no more damage  will
be sustained from the paste.
