"additional"  effects are included at the DM's discretion, but grand  effects
are  never  affected. The somatic concealment proficiency has  no  effect  on
whether  or not a target is perceived as the source of any projected effects;
however,  the  sensory  alteration proficiency can be  used  to  increase  or
decrease  the  intensity of the sensory effects regardless of  the  perceived
source  of  the  effects (see the Dragon Kings source  book,  page  48).  The
material component is a pinch of silt, collected during a silt storm.



