saving  throw  per  se.  Upon first consciously realizing  that  one's  self-
identification  as  male  or female has changed, if the  subject  strenuously
objects, the subject is allowed a Charisma check at -4. A successful Charisma
check  leaves the subject confused but no longer transsexual. A new  Charisma
check may be made each day, but at a cumulative penalty of -1 per day. A roll
of 1 always succeeds.
